1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,760
I'd like to buy
all of Narin Beach Resort's shares back

2
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:01,840
from The One.

3
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,360
Prao and I

4
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:11,480
got a divorce.

5
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:26,160
Please take care of Saifah, Mook.

6
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:28,720
Of course.

7
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,360
Come here.

8
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:44,480
Is there any way you can help Kuk?

9
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:51,000
I'll try talking to my mom.

10
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:56,280
I'm sorry for bothering you
with Kuk's problem.

11
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,600
It's no bother, Mook.

12
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:04,600
Mr. Apichart is Kongkwan's father,
after all.

13
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,280
I'm happy to help anyway.

14
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:43,840
I'm glad we got everything back,

15
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:48,480
and I'm sorry for my mistakes.

16
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:55,800
Actually, you were part of the reason
I got to meet my son again.

17
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,720
You look familiar, Mr. Thee.

18
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,560
Have we met before?

19
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:10,720
<i>I hope you won't forget your promise.</i>

20
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,480
Of course.

21
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:15,760
I promise to take care of this place
and make it better.

22
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,240
Mom!

23
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,200
Good afternoon.

24
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,320
"Mom"?

25
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:25,040
I'll tell you about it later,
Mr. Chadchai,

26
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:27,040
but now, I must ask you to leave.

27
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,600
Of course.

28
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,720
Oh, you mean Mr. Thee?

29
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:36,600
Yes, Thee is my son,
who I've been looking for.

30
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,320
I'm happy for you, Ms. Narin.

31
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:44,240
Mr. Chadchai, can you write
an announcement letter for me?

32
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:47,040
About how we got
all of our shares back, right?

33
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:52,720
About how a new CEO has been appointed
for Narin Beach Resort.

34
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,960
I'm appointing Thee as CEO.

35
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,640
What? But what about you?

36
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:04,360
I'm tired. I've been doing this
for a long time, so I'm stepping down.

37
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:08,720
But don't worry, Mr. Chadchai.
I believe that Thee

38
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:12,200
will do well in running this place
and taking care of everyone here.

39
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,960
Okay, Ms. Narin. I'll take care of it.

40
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,000
‪Thank you.

41
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:23,000
Do you want to renovate
any of the areas here?

42
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,840
You can take it up with Mr. Thee.

43
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,480
Got it.

44
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,720
Didn't Mook come with you?

45
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,240
She has a meeting today.

46
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,440
She'll probably get off work late.

47
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:41,000
That's okay. Can you bring
her along again someday?

48
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,080
I'll cook something good for her.

49
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:46,040
Right now, I've got so many menus in mind.

50
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,160
- Sure, Mom.
- Come on. Let's head inside.

51
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:49,800
Are you tired?

52
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,440
You already came all this way.

53
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,480
Won't you go in and see her?

54
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,760
No, I'm leaving.

55
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,560
Don't tell Thee I came here.

56
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:09,520
Yes, ma'am.

57
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,400
‪Dear me!

58
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:40,120
Kuk, why are you drinking
so early in the day?

59
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:42,200
Aren't you going to work today?

60
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,520
Ma,

61
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,560
I never succeed in anything.

62
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,640
All I do is fail.

63
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,160
I'm good for nothing, Ma.

64
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:56,160
Oh no! Don't say that.
That's a bad thing to say.

65
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,520
Ma.

66
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:03,640
Am I really a dragon
like the master said I was?

67
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,120
Oh my!

68
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:11,480
Your son's the reincarnation of a dragon!

69
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,560
He's truly a rare find!

70
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:17,760
He's the dragon of dragons!

71
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:22,880
He's rich, wealthy,
and he was born to be superior!

72
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,520
I had a family,
but I couldn't take care of them.

73
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,600
And I'm bad at my job too.

74
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,280
Why, Ma?

75
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,080
Why?

76
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,880
Why am I not good at anything?

77
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:48,440
<i>I just want to find a good woman</i>
<i>who's right for my son.</i>

78
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:53,880
A dragon belongs with a swan,
not an earthworm like you.

79
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:59,240
If you think what your son did was right,
then I've got nothing to say to you, Ma.

80
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,840
You can never win
against a dragon like Kuk.

81
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:12,560
I'll show Mook
that leaving me was a mistake.

82
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,200
Ma…

83
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,600
I'm sorry, Ma.

84
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,800
I'm sorry I let you down.

85
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,159
Kuk,

86
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,720
you don't have to apologize.

87
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,520
It's all my fault

88
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:44,080
for raising you this way.

89
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,960
You don't need to be a dragon.

90
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:53,200
Being my son is good enough.

91
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,040
Ma…

92
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,600
It's okay, honey.

93
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:23,800
It's okay. It's okay.

94
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:50,640
About Mr. Apichart's company,
do you think you could help?

95
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,720
Ms. Usa ran away,

96
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:56,560
leaving Mr. Apichart
to handle everything alone.

97
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:04,560
I don't know if I'll be able to help him,
but I'll try talking to Mr. Amnat.

98
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,040
But you must know

99
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:11,720
that Family Tour
will be disqualified from this bid

100
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,280
and any future projects.

101
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,840
Yes, I understand.

102
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:39,360
And what do you want me to do
in return for this favor?

103
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:53,320
Thee only just met his mother again,
yet he seems pretty close to her,

104
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:55,760
unlike when he's with me.

105
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,360
I've raised him all these years,

106
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:02,680
yet we seem so distant,
as if we aren't family.

107
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,880
What makes a family

108
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:14,000
isn't the amount of time
you spend together.

109
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,720
I think family means

110
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:19,520
the love and connection
you have for each other

111
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,360
without expecting anything in return,

112
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:28,680
because people's definition of love
is caring and sharing

113
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,240
rather than investing.

114
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,240
So, it shouldn't involve bargaining
for what you'll get in return.

115
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,400
You adopted him for your own gain,

116
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,200
and it's always been that way,

117
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,680
because every time you gave him something,

118
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:53,640
you'd always do it on a condition.

119
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:09,440
That's why he thinks he's never
received love from a mother like me.

120
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,880
I'm sorry for being so blunt.

121
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:26,440
Nothing.

122
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:33,440
What? Is it so shocking?

123
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:38,480
I just want to help you
without any conditions for a change.

124
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:47,560
Thank you, Mom.

125
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:57,560
Through all this time we've been together,
have you been happy?

126
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:02,440
I've been pretty happy.

127
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:08,080
And I've always been grateful
to you for raising me.

128
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:13,640
Even though I've met my real mother,

129
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:18,800
I'm still Thee, and I'm still your son.

130
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,440
But I won't be the same mother
you used to know.

131
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:33,440
I'll try to be a good mother to you
for a change.

132
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,320
Can I give you a hug?

133
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:14,040
Really? They won't press charges
against us for forging the bid proposal?

134
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,320
Okay. Thank you.

135
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,840
I'm heading to the office now.

136
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:20,600
Wait, wait.

137
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,760
So they won't press charges
against our company now, Kuk?

138
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:23,920
Yes, Ma.

139
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,520
We'll just get disqualified from the bid.

140
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,680
Thank heavens and all the angels!

141
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:32,480
And I thank my ancestors for…

142
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,560
No.

143
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:37,080
We should be thanking Mook
for agreeing to help you.

144
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,920
Mook was the one who helped us?

145
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:44,360
Yes. I went to see her
and begged her to help you.

146
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,640
Your wife sure is reliable, Kuk.

147
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:10,400
Thank you.

148
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,160
Please have a seat, Ma. Kuk.

149
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:30,000
I really appreciate you
for helping Kuk out.

150
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,240
If you hadn't,

151
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:37,520
it would've been over for me and him.

152
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:42,480
Actually, you didn't have to give me this.

153
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:43,880
I was happy to help.

154
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,640
No way.

155
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:50,280
It's tit for tat and quid pro quo.

156
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,240
You helped Kuk,

157
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:56,960
so of course, I'd have a gift
for you in return.

158
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:03,400
If you want to thank someone,
you should thank Mr. Thee.

159
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:05,840
He was the one
who talked to Mrs. Anna for you.

160
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:10,560
Still, I should thank you
for talking to Mr. Thee.

161
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:13,440
You've always helped me,

162
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,600
even though you and our daughter
could never rely on me.

163
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,440
Me too.

164
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,240
In the past,

165
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:33,840
I've done a lot of horrible things to you.

166
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:37,720
I'm sorry.

167
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:40,920
Please forgive me.

168
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:47,080
If anyone is to blame,

169
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,200
it's me,

170
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:54,560
who caused all this mess.

171
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,920
Ma, it's okay.

172
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:09,920
If I'd raised him well
and set a good example for my son,

173
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:14,960
instead of raising him to have
a warped sense of right and wrong…

174
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:20,160
Kuk wouldn't have turned out this way.

175
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,319
It's okay, Ma.

176
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:33,160
Let's not mention what's in the past.

177
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:38,600
As for Usa,

178
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,960
I won't let her get away so easily.

179
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:46,120
But we don't have
any evidence against her, Ma.

180
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:50,840
I was the one who signed
all the documents.

181
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:57,920
You don't, but I do.

182
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:27,840
I'm really sorry, Mrs. Anna,
for asking you to meet here.

183
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:30,520
I didn't want Thee to know.

184
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,400
What did you want to talk about?

185
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:37,640
Ever since I met my son,

186
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,440
I haven't had the chance
to have a proper conversation with you.

187
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:48,440
I wanted to thank you for raising Saifah…

188
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,880
I mean, Thee, so well.

189
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:54,440
If I hadn't gotten in an accident,

190
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:59,240
who knows how hard
he would be struggling right now.

191
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:08,040
Thee was lucky to be adopted by you.

192
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:13,840
But what I wanted to tell you

193
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:17,280
is that I never wanted
to take him away from you.

194
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:25,760
After all, I think he's very lucky

195
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:30,560
to have two mothers
who love him very much.

196
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:35,600
And I believe that's also what he thinks.

197
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:39,800
I didn't raise him
as well as you think I did.

198
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,520
Up until now,

199
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,000
I've only raised him physically.

200
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:48,280
I supported him financially

201
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:53,640
and gave him a good social status
along with a comfortable life.

202
00:19:57,600 --> 00:20:00,480
But I think what I never gave him

203
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:07,280
is the love and warmth
that a mother should give her child.

204
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:16,560
So, why don't we both compensate him

205
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,880
with what we never gave him before?

206
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,000
What do you think?

207
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:58,280
Okay.

208
00:20:58,360 --> 00:21:00,640
I'm holding onto it, so don't be afraid.

209
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,960
Keep going way further. Like that.

210
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:07,520
Whirr… Okay.

211
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,520
I'm letting go this time.

212
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:13,840
Ready?

213
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,400
Go.

214
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:22,560
Okay.

215
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:24,880
Ride back toward me.

216
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:28,520
Come on. Do a U-turn.

217
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,080
Yeah! Way to go!

218
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:34,120
Yay! I did it!

219
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,240
- Yay!
- Yay!

220
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:36,360
Way to go.

221
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:39,200
Mr. Thee. Kongkwan. Let's eat.

222
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:44,320
Mommy, I can ride my bike now.

223
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,880
Really? Way to go.

224
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:49,160
But right now, we need to have lunch,

225
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:51,840
or else your grandma will spank all of us.

226
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,320
Ooh, we'll get spanked!

227
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,360
- Come on.
- Wanna go?

228
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,520
Okay. Let Thee handle it. Let's go.

229
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:58,360
- Come on.
- What's the hurry?

230
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:00,320
- You left your bike.
- Go to Grandma.

231
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,680
Let me close the gate.

232
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:13,880
Kuk!

233
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,400
- Oh, thank you.
- Thanks.

234
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:36,600
Your cooking's still as good as ever.

235
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:47,520
Kongkwan,

236
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,560
I brought you a gift.

237
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:55,040
Thank you, Daddy.

238
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,760
Look.

239
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,240
Do you like it?

240
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,480
I do,

241
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:05,280
but now, I prefer playing with Legos.

242
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:15,120
As our daughter grows up, it's natural
that her favorite toy will change.

243
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:22,360
Anyway, if you'll excuse me.

244
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:24,640
I'll get going now.

245
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:28,960
Mr. Thee, do you have a minute?

246
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:30,320
I'd like to talk to you.

247
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:43,000
Honestly, I wanted my family back.

248
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:45,360
But I'm well aware

249
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,520
that I have no right
to ask anything of Mook.

250
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:54,080
Since we got married,

251
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:58,000
I've been well aware
that she beats me at everything.

252
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:01,760
Why do you have to compare
yourself to her?

253
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,320
Why didn't you want to build a life

254
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:08,760
and deal with problems
and obstacles together?

255
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:13,600
After all, that's what really matters
in a relationship.

256
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:18,800
I tried to do everything
to compensate for my weaknesses

257
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:22,880
to show Mook
that I'm not weaker than anyone.

258
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:25,240
But I was wrong about everything.

259
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:31,000
I don't know
how your relationship was like,

260
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:35,840
but I do know that Mook
is a talented and skilled woman.

261
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:40,520
I think it's better if we can accept
each other's strengths

262
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,120
and weaknesses.

263
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:48,440
At least, now I'm glad
to see that Mook and Kongkwan are happy.

264
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:55,560
Thank you, Mr. Thee,
for making those two smile again.

265
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:04,080
Now I know what is truly Mook's happiness.

266
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:07,280
You didn't lose your family, though.

267
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:10,920
Kongkwan is still your daughter,
no matter what.

268
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:16,600
You can still be a good father
and a good friend of Mook's.

269
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,200
Sure.

270
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:22,520
I may have failed the test
for being a good husband,

271
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:25,280
but I'll try my best to be a good father.

272
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,640
‪-I'll get going now, Mook.
‪-Okay.

273
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,320
What was that long talk about?

274
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:29,200
I'm really lucky to have known you
and get to love you.

275
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:31,520
I promise

276
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:36,160
I'll never leave
the most precious thing in my life.

277
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,160
I used to blame myself

278
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:53,240
for choosing the wrong path
and failing in life because of it.

279
00:26:55,800 --> 00:27:00,040
I lost all self-respect and self-esteem.

280
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:06,400
Sometimes, to find the answers in life,

281
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:12,000
you must learn to lose something first.

282
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:17,080
But it was worth it

283
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:23,000
because it taught me
to be more careful with my next steps.

284
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,880
So, are you ready to take a step further?

285
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:38,640
Will you marry me, Mook?

286
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,000
Mr. Pitak.

287
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,560
Where'd my belongings go?

288
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:26,320
Mrs. Anna said
you must move into a new office

289
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,320
to match your new title.

290
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:29,320
My new title?

291
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:31,400
What does that mean?

292
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:34,320
You might want to ask her
yourself, Mr. Thee.

293
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:39,200
But you'll have to wait
because she's with an important guest.

294
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,240
Sorry for asking to see you
on such short notice.

295
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:55,120
Pitak told me you would be here
for the signing anyway.

296
00:28:56,240 --> 00:29:00,360
Yes. Mr. Thee invited me and Mr. Pat here
to talk about the project too.

297
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:04,720
I know I've wronged you many times.

298
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:09,800
But let me put it simply.

299
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:14,560
I think I should love
whoever my son loves.

300
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:23,240
Thee loves you very much,

301
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:27,800
so much that he'd disobey me.

302
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,320
I'm sorry

303
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:36,920
for causing you and Mr. Thee
to have a falling-out, Mrs. Anna.

304
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,560
"Mom."

305
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:42,520
Yes?

306
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,240
Pardon me?

307
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:51,160
Call me "Mom", like Thee does.

308
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:55,560
Mook.

309
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,160
When did you get here?

310
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,400
Why didn't you call me?

311
00:30:00,320 --> 00:30:03,480
Mrs. Anna told me
to bring Mook to see her first.

312
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:09,240
Good, you're here.

313
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,880
I had Pitak move your office.

314
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:18,120
You'll need to be back here
to run TJ Group like before.

315
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:21,560
But this time, you'll have to do it alone.

316
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:26,000
I want to step down.

317
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:27,560
I want to rest.

318
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:41,720
I hope having two moms isn't too tiring.

319
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:48,160
Go already, Pitak. It's about to start.

320
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:49,840
Understood.

321
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:05,840
Did my mom scare you?

322
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:10,600
Yes.

323
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:14,280
What'd she say?

324
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:18,640
She told me…

325
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,240
to call her "Mom", like you do.

326
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,400
Stop teasing me.

327
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:42,000
SIGNATURE - MR. JOE M. VICTOR
SIGNATURE - MR. THEECHUDA TEERASU

328
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:44,680
PRESS CONFERENCE FOR THE SIGNING BETWEEN
VICTORIA INDUSTRY GROUP & TJ GROUP

329
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:54,680
Congratulations, Ms. Mook.

330
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:58,000
Thee told me you said yes to marrying him.

331
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:00,640
Thank you, Ms. Bell.

332
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:03,520
I volunteer to design your wedding dress.

333
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,680
I'll make it as pretty as I can.

334
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:07,680
Sure,

335
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:12,040
but after you design mine,
don't forget to design yours too.

336
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:15,120
I think someone's waiting.

337
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:19,320
Stop teasing me, Mook.

338
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:55,680
I'll drive you to the studio,
then I'll pick Poonpun up from school.

339
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:59,160
Prao told me she has an important meeting,

340
00:32:59,240 --> 00:33:01,080
so she wanted me to pick him up.

341
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:03,040
You don't have to drive me.

342
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,680
I don't want you to pick him up late.

343
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:05,960
I can go on my own.

344
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:12,120
Then, how about we go
pick Poonpun up together?

345
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,880
Sounds good. I wanted to see him anyway.

346
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:27,680
I called this urgent meeting today

347
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:33,200
because I've made my decision
regarding our party's candidate,

348
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:37,120
who's running for office.

349
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:40,160
So Mr. Anapat changed his mind
and decided to run?

350
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:44,360
With this candidate, I can assure you

351
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:48,320
that she's got
the same fighting spirit that I have.

352
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:52,400
Oh! It's Ms. Prao.

353
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:54,560
- A familiar face.
- A familiar face.

354
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:04,960
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

355
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:11,639
I look forward to working with you all.
I will do my best.

356
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:18,560
Please welcome our new member

357
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:24,639
and our candidate who's running for office
on behalf of the Ruam Jai party.

358
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:28,400
RUAM JAI PARTY - COLLABORATE
AND HELP IMPROVE THE THAI SOCIETY

359
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:34,120
‪Thank you.

360
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:50,800
- He should be done any time now.
- Okay.

361
00:34:52,040 --> 00:34:53,719
- Hang tight.
- Sure.

362
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:07,800
I've never seen that woman before.

363
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:11,320
But why do they seem so close?

364
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,720
I'd better look into it.

365
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:24,360
Hello, Mr. Pat.

366
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:25,320
Hello.

367
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:28,000
You're picking Poonpun up today?

368
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:29,880
Yes, I am.

369
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:37,800
This is my girlfriend, Bell.

370
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,400
- And does--
- Prao already knows.

371
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:49,920
Well, Mr. Pat, that's a personal matter.

372
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:53,080
You didn't have to tell us.

373
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:56,000
Well, I've got nothing to hide anyway.

374
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,680
I told you so you don't have to assume.

375
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:04,960
‪Mommy!

376
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,800
- Kids!
- Hi.

377
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,720
Our kids are here.
So, if you'll excuse me.

378
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:10,680
Of course.

379
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,880
Daddy!

380
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:20,800
- Hello.
- Hello, Poonpun.

381
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:26,760
This… This is Aunt Bell. She's my friend.

382
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,640
Hello, Aunt Bell.

383
00:36:29,240 --> 00:36:30,360
Hello, Poonpun.

384
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:36,160
Poonpun, let's go
get something good to eat.

385
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,280
Sounds good.

386
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:38,360
What do you want to eat?

387
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:39,840
- Pizza?
- Pizza, please.

388
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:44,480
Since you're on the same page,
wanna go now?

389
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:47,040
- Yes, please.
- Let's go.

390
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:50,120
What toppings do you like on your pizza?

391
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,640
Cheese.

392
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:54,280
Wow! Melty cheese, right?

393
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:55,400
Yeah!

394
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,160
Mr. Thee's a good guy.

395
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:13,320
I'm happy for you
for finding a good guy like him.

396
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:19,840
I never thought you were a bad guy.

397
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:23,840
Maybe we needed more time
to get to know each other,

398
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:28,400
and we were too young
to deal with the problems.

399
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:32,160
It was my fault, Mook,

400
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:35,080
for taking my family for granted.

401
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:43,160
But from now on, I'll try to be better.

402
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,680
I can still start over, right, Mook?

403
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:49,840
Of course, Kuk.

404
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:52,760
From now on, I hope
only good things come your way.

405
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:55,440
Thanks, Mook.

406
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,520
You got this.

407
00:37:58,240 --> 00:37:59,280
Daddy!

408
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:02,480
Good afternoon.

409
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:04,280
Good afternoon.

410
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:06,440
I'll take you out today.

411
00:38:06,520 --> 00:38:08,080
- Sure.
- Are you ready?

412
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,200
Good afternoon, Mom.

413
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:16,240
I'll drive her home before it gets late.

414
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:17,240
Okay.

415
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:20,800
Kongkwan, be good, okay?

416
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:23,440
- Listen to your daddy.
- Okay.

417
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:29,960
Let's go. Let's go on a trip.

418
00:38:34,560 --> 00:38:36,040
Will they really be okay?

419
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:38,600
Of course they will, Mom.

420
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,720
She looks really happy.

421
00:38:58,600 --> 00:38:59,440
Ma!

422
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:02,600
What are you doing here?

423
00:39:02,680 --> 00:39:04,240
Were you arrested for gambling again?

424
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:06,960
Hey! That's not it, Kuk.

425
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:09,560
I'm here to see
the thief's face, of course.

426
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:11,480
Thief?

427
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:13,440
Let me go, Officer!

428
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,320
- Let me go! I really didn't do it!
- This way, please.

429
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,400
- Usa.
- I really didn't do it! Please, please!

430
00:39:18,480 --> 00:39:20,360
- Please… Kuk!
- Usa.

431
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:23,080
Please help me, Kuk.
I really didn't do it.

432
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:26,760
There's concrete evidence,
yet you have the nerve to deny it?

433
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:29,360
What evidence, Ma?

434
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:33,440
Evidence that she stole
from me, of course!

435
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:37,480
I really didn't do it.
You have to believe me, Kuk.

436
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:40,120
You have to believe me.
I didn't do it. Let me go!

437
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:43,760
Don't scratch the paint.

438
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,960
Okay. We're all set. Should be good now.

439
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:53,120
You're all set, ma'am.

440
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,200
What a relief.

441
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:57,080
Ever since my daughter-in-law moved in,

442
00:39:57,160 --> 00:39:58,440
I haven't been able to sleep.

443
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:00,040
I'm scared she'll steal from me.

444
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:03,080
With a camera, you can be at ease.

445
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,680
Everyone installs it nowadays, ma'am.

446
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:06,000
Yeah.

447
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:12,000
Kuk, please help me.

448
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:14,040
I really didn't do it, Kuk!

449
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:15,400
- Believe me!
- Who would've thought

450
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:18,120
the one stealing from me wasn't Mook,

451
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:19,520
but it was you, Usa.

452
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:21,560
That's not true! Don't believe her, Kuk.

453
00:40:21,640 --> 00:40:23,080
I was just borrowing them.

454
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:25,520
I earned more money so I could help you.

455
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:28,640
I love you, Kuk. Please believe me.

456
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:32,000
I love you, Kuk. Please help me.

457
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:35,280
You really think I'd still believe you?

458
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:39,360
I never thought
you'd be this kind of person.

459
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:41,320
I won't let you off easy.

460
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:43,880
Please take her, Officer.

461
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:48,000
- This way, please.
- No! Kuk! Let go! Help me! I didn't do it!

462
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:51,040
Kuk, help me! I didn't do it!

463
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,840
I had a lot of fun yesterday.

464
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:11,520
Daddy even told me
he'd take me on a trip again.

465
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:15,560
Of course. But it's very late.

466
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:17,960
For now, you have to go to bed. Okay?

467
00:41:18,040 --> 00:41:20,200
When will Thee come over again?

468
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:25,000
Lately, he's been busy with work.

469
00:41:25,080 --> 00:41:27,800
Once he's done, he'll come
see you as soon as he can.

470
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:29,280
What a shame.

471
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:32,240
I wish he could come see me every day.

472
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:40,400
If he was here with you every day,
would you be happy?

473
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:41,920
Of course I'd be happy.

474
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,520
I like having Thee around.

475
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:47,800
He plays with me and eats snacks with me.

476
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:50,760
He also helps me with my homework
and tells me stories.

477
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:54,680
I like being with Thee. I love him.

478
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:57,320
So,

479
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:03,640
if I marry him,
will you be okay with that?

480
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:06,000
If it's Thee, then sure.

481
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:10,560
Thank you, honey.

482
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:13,760
I love you more
than anything in the world.

483
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:16,240
I love you more
than anything in the world too.

484
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:51,360
I think we should make it
a cute and small wedding.

485
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:53,920
Candles and beautiful flowers
could also make it chic.

486
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:57,000
Or we could make it a beach wedding.

487
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:58,960
Mook loves the beach!

488
00:43:00,280 --> 00:43:02,560
How about a Chinese banquet?

489
00:43:02,640 --> 00:43:06,520
Let's treat the guests super well
and book with the priciest hotels.

490
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:09,680
Wow! Whose wedding is this again?

491
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:11,360
Mook and Mr. Thee, of course.

492
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:14,400
So, why don't you ask them?

493
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:22,400
- There she is!
- Good, you're all here.

494
00:43:22,480 --> 00:43:24,440
I just got briefed by our new client.

495
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:26,520
I'll start the meeting, then.

496
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:29,400
Mook, forget the new project.

497
00:43:29,480 --> 00:43:31,240
Let's talk about the wedding.

498
00:43:33,520 --> 00:43:34,560
Whose wedding is it?

499
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:37,560
What? Yours and Mr. Thee's wedding,
of course!

500
00:43:40,840 --> 00:43:42,120
Who said there'd be a wedding?

501
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:55,680
You're not getting married?

502
00:43:55,760 --> 00:43:57,560
That's not it, Mom.

503
00:43:57,640 --> 00:44:00,040
We just want a small, laid-back wedding.

504
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:03,560
You can't do that, honey.

505
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:05,360
That's disrespectful to Mook.

506
00:44:06,800 --> 00:44:09,120
I was the one who told him.

507
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:14,960
As you're all aware,
Mook's gotten married before,

508
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,920
and that marriage
didn't turn out to be successful

509
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,680
like she'd expected.

510
00:44:23,800 --> 00:44:26,040
Are you still afraid of remarrying, honey?

511
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:31,040
No, that's not it.

512
00:44:31,720 --> 00:44:36,600
I just think that
when two people share a life together,

513
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:39,680
marriage doesn't guarantee your happiness.

514
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:47,040
Mook and I think that
as long as we love each other

515
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:49,680
and understand each other,
that's good enough.

516
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,320
We don't need a huge wedding.

517
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:58,960
We just want to thank our friends
and family, who we love,

518
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:01,280
for getting us here today.

519
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:13,800
If you don't mind, Mook and I

520
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:15,720
would like to plan
our own kind of wedding.

521
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:29,400
You can plan any kind of wedding.

522
00:45:29,480 --> 00:45:31,400
I'll leave it up to you and Mook.

523
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:34,280
But I want just one thing,

524
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:39,200
which is for you to have
a successful relationship this time.

525
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:43,760
Take care of each other
and be considerate.

526
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:48,520
Whether there's a ceremony or not,

527
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,680
I'm happy for you either way.

528
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:04,960
‪Thank you, Mom.

529
00:46:14,280 --> 00:46:18,480
In that case,
I'll leave it up to you to decide.

530
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:22,960
After all, this is the start
of a new life…

531
00:46:25,080 --> 00:46:26,680
for both of you.

532
00:46:36,240 --> 00:46:42,360
May you both be happy
with the choice you've made.

533
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:47,680
Always figure things out
and make decisions together, okay?

534
00:46:50,840 --> 00:46:52,880
Thank you for understanding.

535
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:47,120
I'm so touched! How cute!

536
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:48,560
That's great.

537
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:51,400
Then, let's do the same for our wedding.

538
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:54,160
A small budget to keep it safe.

539
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:56,000
- Take that! No!
- Hey!

540
00:47:56,080 --> 00:47:57,600
I want to wear a wedding dress.

541
00:47:57,680 --> 00:47:58,920
Okay, okay. Sure.

542
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:05,480
Hey! What?!

543
00:48:08,560 --> 00:48:11,560
She's blushing. She is.

544
00:48:11,640 --> 00:48:13,360
What, Mr. Suetrong?

545
00:48:14,720 --> 00:48:17,840
Nothing. Go for it. Get a wedding dress.

546
00:48:19,720 --> 00:48:21,880
- Boss, what about our dress--
- Stop it.

547
00:48:23,960 --> 00:48:25,200
There goes my joke, boss.

548
00:48:27,560 --> 00:48:31,320
Could it be you want to wear
a wedding dress, Mr. Suetrong?

549
00:48:31,400 --> 00:48:34,440
Yass! Bring me the dress, sis.
Where is it?

550
00:48:50,400 --> 00:48:53,640
Are you sure about having
such a small wedding, Mook?

551
00:48:55,280 --> 00:48:57,960
I know, right? I really don't get you.

552
00:48:58,040 --> 00:49:00,080
Mr. Thee's stinking rich.

553
00:49:00,160 --> 00:49:03,440
Why don't you have a huge wedding
befitting his wealth?

554
00:49:03,520 --> 00:49:05,720
Because I think it's unnecessary.

555
00:49:07,080 --> 00:49:10,800
I know Mr. Thee loves me,
and I love him too.

556
00:49:11,880 --> 00:49:14,760
I just don't think marriage
is the ultimate answer in a relationship.

557
00:49:17,440 --> 00:49:18,920
That's true.

558
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:20,520
Take me and my ex, for example.

559
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:23,480
Not only was it not great,
it was a disaster.

560
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:28,800
That's true.

561
00:49:29,840 --> 00:49:34,760
There's no guarantee
what life after marriage will be like.

562
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:39,920
I guess it's up to the couple,
like you said.

563
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:43,920
- Mook.
- Yes?

564
00:49:44,520 --> 00:49:48,080
I wish you happiness every single day.

565
00:49:50,240 --> 00:49:51,440
Me too.

566
00:49:53,640 --> 00:49:57,840
Thank you for never leaving me, you two.

567
00:50:00,800 --> 00:50:02,200
I love you so much.

568
00:50:21,520 --> 00:50:23,840
Just like that.

569
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:29,720
- When did you get here?
- There's coffee.

570
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:33,400
- Oh! I forgot to tell you.
- This one looks really good.

571
00:50:33,480 --> 00:50:34,680
- This was made by
- Excuse me.

572
00:50:34,760 --> 00:50:36,560
- Narin Beach Resort.
- Can I take a picture?

573
00:50:36,640 --> 00:50:38,200
- Sure.
- Of course.

574
00:50:38,280 --> 00:50:40,160
- Please look at this camera.
- Yes.

575
00:50:40,240 --> 00:50:42,440
One, two, three.

576
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:45,440
- Perfect.
- Thank you.

577
00:50:45,520 --> 00:50:47,680
- Make sure I look pretty.
- Let's go, Whan.

578
00:50:47,760 --> 00:50:50,200
Can I take a picture of you?

579
00:50:50,280 --> 00:50:52,360
Kongkwan. Poonpun. Smile, honey.

580
00:50:52,440 --> 00:50:55,120
One, two, three. Hold up your fingers.

581
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:56,360
One, two, three.

582
00:50:56,440 --> 00:50:58,160
Can we take a selfie?

583
00:50:58,800 --> 00:51:02,080
Come on. One, two, three.

584
00:51:04,000 --> 00:51:05,680
- Boss.
- Yes?

585
00:51:05,760 --> 00:51:07,840
- Can I take a photo of you?
- Sure.

586
00:51:07,920 --> 00:51:10,120
Both of you, please. Both of you together.

587
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:11,040
Look at the camera.

588
00:51:11,120 --> 00:51:12,640
Hug her. Hug her a little.

589
00:51:13,240 --> 00:51:16,040
Perfect. One more, please.
One, two, three.

590
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:21,840
You're so good!

591
00:51:21,920 --> 00:51:24,600
I haven't started. I'm just tuning it.

592
00:51:27,280 --> 00:51:28,120
Are we not done yet?

593
00:51:28,200 --> 00:51:30,040
- One, two, three.
- Good.

594
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:31,880
- Perfect.
- Do you want one too?

595
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:36,560
- Thank you!
- You look great.

596
00:51:36,640 --> 00:51:38,840
Wow. You two are so sweet together.

597
00:51:38,920 --> 00:51:41,480
- Really.
- Sugar's got nothing on you.

598
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:44,720
You're feeding her and all.

599
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:30,560
I'm so happy today, Mook.

600
00:52:32,520 --> 00:52:34,400
I'm really happy too.

601
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:36,360
Thank you.

602
00:52:44,520 --> 00:52:47,000
I'm the one who should thank you

603
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:50,840
for believing in me.

604
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:54,840
And thank you for having faith in my love.

605
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:58,880
I love you, Mook.

606
00:53:00,680 --> 00:53:02,240
I love you too.

607
00:53:02,320 --> 00:53:03,760
- Give me a spin!
- Yeah!

608
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:21,440
Kuk called me.

609
00:53:26,840 --> 00:53:30,120
<i>Sorry, Mook. I just so happened</i>
<i>to have a group tour today,</i>

610
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:31,520
<i>so I couldn't make it.</i>

611
00:53:31,600 --> 00:53:33,920
May you and Mr. Thee be very happy.

612
00:53:34,640 --> 00:53:35,680
I'm sorry, Mook.

613
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:36,840
Excuse me.

614
00:53:36,920 --> 00:53:37,840
<i>Thank you.</i>

615
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:38,800
- <i>Thank you.</i>
- Kuk.

616
00:53:38,880 --> 00:53:41,080
It's time to get in the car, honey.

617
00:53:41,160 --> 00:53:42,560
Hello, Ma.

618
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:47,040
<i>Oh! May you be very happy, Mook, Mr. Thee.</i>

619
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:49,960
<i>May you be blessed</i>
<i>with the patter of tiny feet.</i>

620
00:53:50,040 --> 00:53:51,120
Thank you.

621
00:53:51,200 --> 00:53:53,640
Hurry, honey. Your clients are waiting.

622
00:53:53,720 --> 00:53:54,640
Okay, Ma.

623
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:56,560
I'll get back to work now, Mook.

624
00:53:56,640 --> 00:53:58,520
- Congratulations again.
- Hey, Jeng.

625
00:53:58,600 --> 00:54:00,040
See you later. Bye.

626
00:54:00,120 --> 00:54:02,080
Thank you. Bye.

627
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:09,840
Mrs. Tiansee wished us
the patter of tiny feet.

628
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:10,840
Wanna start tonight?

629
00:54:11,800 --> 00:54:13,680
- Cheeky!
- I'm serious!

630
00:54:16,160 --> 00:54:17,440
Look. Look at them instead.

631
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:21,240
Mook. Mr. Thee.
Let's have some barbecue together.

632
00:54:21,320 --> 00:54:22,200
Let's go.

633
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:44,880
Let's take a photo, everyone.

634
00:55:30,400 --> 00:55:34,880
<i>Many women dream of meeting a good man</i>

635
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:37,840
<i>in hopes to get married</i>
<i>and have a good family life.</i>

636
00:55:38,800 --> 00:55:41,160
<i>But if it doesn't turn out to be</i>
<i>what you dreamed of,</i>

637
00:55:41,240 --> 00:55:45,000
<i>that doesn't mean</i>
<i>you can never be happy again in life.</i>

638
00:55:45,080 --> 00:55:49,440
<i>Try to keep an open mind</i>
<i>and start loving someone new.</i>

639
00:58:16,080 --> 00:58:21,200
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
